data.name: label2.Text
data.value:
This wizard will assist you in the creation and upload process of a DotNetNuke Community instance on Windows Azure Platform.
On the next steps, you must specify the configuration parameters for the instances, so you should be familiar with the DNN Azure deployment architecture. If you have any doubt, please visit http://dnnazureaccelerator.codeplex.com/ for more information.
Click the Next button to begin the process.

data.name: label62.Text
data.value: Select the DotNetNuke version that you want to deploy into Azure or specify a custom Url. The zip file containing the DNN distribution package will be downloaded and unzipped directly from Azure (if you use custom, make sure to introduce a public Url).

data.name: label47.Text
data.value: Enabling Azure Connect allows you to connect from on-premise computers or other cloud instances. This is very useful for doing certain maintenance tasks on the roles like mapping the VHD drive on your local computer for updating the contents.
